diagnoses.label: C4-C5 cervical spondylosis
evidence_spans: At C4-C5, there were minimal uncovertebral osteophytes with mild associated right foraminal compromise.

diagnoses.label: C5-C6 cervical spondylosis
evidence_spans: At C5-C6, there were minimal diffuse disc bulge and uncovertebral osteophytes with indentation of the anterior thecal sac, but no cord deformity or foraminal compromise.

diagnoses.label: C6-C7 cervical spondylosis
evidence_spans: At C6-C7, there was a central disc herniation resulting in mild deformity of the anterior aspect of the cord with patent neuroforamina.

diagnoses.label: T5-T6 disc generation
evidence_spans: There was evidence of disc generation, especially anteriorly at the T5-T6 level.

diagnoses.label: L4-L5 disc herniation
evidence_spans: There was a right paracentral disc protrusion at L4-L5 narrowing of the right lateral recess.

diagnoses.label: L5-S1 disc herniation
evidence_spans: There was also a central disc protrusion seen at the L5-S1 level resulting in indentation of the anterior thecal sac and minimal bilateral foraminal compromise.

patient_summary: The patient had an MRI of the cervical, thoracic, and lumbar spine. The MRI showed some mild changes in the spine, but nothing that would cause serious problems. The patient needs to follow up with their doctor to discuss the results of the MRI.
notes: The MRI findings are consistent with the patient's symptoms. The patient should follow up with their doctor to discuss the results of the MRI and any further treatment that may be needed. The patient is being discharged home.
